Fears around the Anti-polio-initiative in Afghanistan 
In the youngest Anti-polio-initiative in Afghanistan, almost 200,000 children were not vaccinated based on the force, that is connected with the Taliban,, so the United Nations. 
The United Nations carried out last week a vaccinate program in six provinces. 
However they not for safety reasons were able to reach children in parts of Helmand and Kandahar in the south. 
According to a speaker of the UN, this was the case in spite of the promise of the Taliban not to attack and/or to hinder the thousands colleague carrying out the vaccinations. 
